description:
&lt;h1&gt;Head of Continuous Improvement&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you’re an exceptional leader with a deep technical knowledge of and passion for improvement, coupled with an ability to inspire others, then take your next career step with us! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;At Portsmouth we’ve been working hard to improve our care for our patients and our communities and are proud of achieving a “Good” CQC rating. But we don’t want to stop there. Our Trust vision is &lt;em&gt;Working together to drive excellence in care for our patients and communities&lt;/em&gt;. To achieve excellence, we know we need to develop our Trust-wide approach to managing our quality through continuous improvement of our day-to-day actions, functions, and processes - and through the engagement and enthusiasm of our staff. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’ve already made a start on our &lt;em&gt;Delivering Excellence&lt;/em&gt; system and have invested in a core team to develop and embed our approach. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Head of Continuous Improvement will have responsibility for the development and leadership of the Trust’s approach to continuous improvement within the Delivering Excellence system. The role will lead the establishment and ongoing development of the core team and support the implementation of Delivering Excellence across the organisation through the provision of continuous improvement expertise. Taking responsibility for building improvement capability and capacity across services, you will lead a core Delivering Excellence team providing expert coaching, training and facilitation of improvement across the organisation in line with the Trust’s strategic priorities. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A background in healthcare is not essential, but the experience of working across a complex organisation in the field of continuous improvement is. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 16th November 2020&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date - 2 December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
